text:
STARSHIP STOP BEING A COWARD AND ISSUE AN OFFICIAL APOLOGY TO YUJIN !

context:
Starship official Weibo account reposted deepfake / s*xually edited photo of  An Yujin.
To know how serious this is and to put into perspective 
Imagine your coworker just 'accidentally' share deepfake / s*exually edited photo of yours, that was intended to humiliate you, in a workplace where you have to work everyday, that's just pure evil

The way starship is handing the aftermath of this situation is WORST
1)issued a apology full of excuses saying that they wanted to report but accidentally clicked repost(which is not possible cause you have to double confirm twice in order to repost)

*they did not even mention yujin's name and  said they apologise to those who "may" be affected LIKE WTF THE AUDACITY 

2)disabled the comment section of that apology post to protect themselves from people calling them out
(People have been begging starship to disable the comment section on yujin's post cause her antis are ruthless there and defame and make fun of her unsparingly
Yujin has been heavily targeted by antis on Chinese community, yet the company didn't do anything to protect her, for years.

*yujin's fanbase in china have been collecting those defamation post and have been sending them to starship in hopes they will take legal action but they IGNORED*

3)paid money to make their no.1 Trending on weibo about the incident disappear
